{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T11:17:27.903Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Encoder/Decoder — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Encoder/Decoder in Autoencoders Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Encoder/Decoder"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in Autoencoders refers to the two primary neural network components that work together to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "compress input data into essential features and then reconstruct it"}, {"type": "text", "text": " from that compressed representation. Unlike Seq2Seq models where encoder and decoder handle different sequences (e.g., English → French), autoencoders use them for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "input → compressed representation → same input reconstruction"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Encoder/Decoder Matters in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Encoder/Decoder in autoencoders is fundamental for generative AI because it:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Capability"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Application"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Dimensionality reduction"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Compresses high-dimensional data (images, videos) to compact representations"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Feature extraction"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Learns efficient data representations without manual labeling"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Noise removal"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Extracts main features and reconstructs less noisy versions"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Data generation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Latent space can generate new samples by sampling and decoding"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Anomaly detection"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Identify unusual patterns via poor reconstruction"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Encoder Works (Core Mechanics)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Encoder: Your Data's Summarizer"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Details"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Role"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Takes input data and compresses it into a lower-dimensional representation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Function"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradually reduces dimensions through layers with fewer neurons"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Output"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Latent representation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (also called \"coding\" or \"compressed summary\")"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "z = e(X)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " where "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "X"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " is input, "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "e"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " is encoder, "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "z"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " is compressed representation"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "How it works"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Input: Image with many pixels (e.g., 784 dimensions for 28×28 image)\n- Processing: Each layer has fewer units than the previous\n- Output: Compressed vector (e.g., 32 dimensions)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Goal"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Make "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "z"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "much smaller than "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "X"}}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": " in dimensionality without losing the essence of information."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Encoder Flow:\nInput (784 pixels) → Layer 1 (128 units) → Layer 2 (64 units) → Latent Space (32 units)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The encoder learns to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "map input to lower-dimensional latent space"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (the bottleneck)."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Bottleneck (Latent Space)"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Details"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Definition"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The narrowest part of autoencoder, where compressed representation resides"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Also called"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\"Latent space\", \"coding layer\", \"embedding\""}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Role"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Holds the learned compressed features"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Size"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fixed dimensionality (e.g., 32, 64, 128) regardless of input size"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Autoencoder Architecture:\n┌──────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ ENCODER (compression)                │\n│  Input → Hidden Layers → Latent Space│\n│  (784)  (128, 64)    (32) ← BOTTLENECK│\n└──────────────────────────────────────┘\n                                    ↓\n┌──────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ DECODER (reconstruction)             │\n│  Latent → Hidden Layers → Output     │\n│  (32)   (64, 128)    (784)           │\n└──────────────────────────────────────┘"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The bottleneck is where the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "most compact, distilled version"}, {"type": "text", "text": " of your data resides."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Decoder Works (Core Mechanics)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Decoder: Data Reconstructor"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Details"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Role"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Takes compressed summary and reconstructs original data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Function"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Opposite of encoder: expands low-dimensional data back to original high-dimensional form"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Input"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Latent representation "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "z"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " from bottleneck"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Output"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reconstruction "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "X'"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " (attempted copy of original input)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "X' = d(z)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " where "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "d"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " is decoder"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "How it works"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Input: Compressed vector (32 dimensions)\n- Processing: Each layer has "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "more units"}, {"type": "text", "text": " than the previous (mirrors encoder in reverse)\n- Output: Reconstructed image (784 dimensions)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Structure"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Decoder often "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "mirrors encoder's structure but in reverse"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- If encoder had layers reducing units (784 → 128 → 64 → 32)\n- Decoder has layers increasing units (32 → 64 → 128 → 784)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Decoder Flow:\nLatent Space (32 units) → Layer 1 (64 units) → Layer 2 (128 units) → Output (784 pixels)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The goal is to make "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "X'"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "close to original "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "X"}}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": " as possible."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Encoder vs. Decoder Comparison"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Property"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Encoder"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Decoder"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Direction"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Compresses (high → low dimension)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Expands (low → high dimension)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Layers"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Progressive reduction of units"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Progressive increase of units"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Output"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Latent representation "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "z"}}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reconstruction "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "X'"}}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Goal"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Learn compact representation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reconstruct original data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Reverse"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Original direction"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mirrors encoder in reverse"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Training Process"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The autoencoder is trained to bring the output as close to the input as possible:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Training Loop:\n1. Input: X (original image)\n2. Encoder: z = e(X) (compress to 32 units)\n3. Decoder: X' = d(z) (reconstruct to 784 units)\n4. Loss: Compare X' with X (e.g., mean squared error)\n5. Update: Minimize loss via backpropagation\n\nGoal: Minimize ||X - X'||²"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Loss function"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Mean squared error (MSE) between input and output:\n\\[\n\\text{Loss} = \\text{MSE}(X, X') = \\frac{1}{n} \\sum"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{i=1}^{n} (X_i - X'"}, {"type": "text", "text": "i)^2\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "If the decoder successfully reconstructs the original data from the compressed version, the bottleneck contains a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "useful, information-rich representation"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example: Image Compression with Autoencoder"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Input Image:\n  28×28 pixels = 784 dimensions\n  (raw pixel values)\n\nEncoder:\n  Layer 1: 784 → 128 units\n  Layer 2: 128 → 64 units\n  Bottleneck: 64 → 32 units (compressed)\n  \nLatent Representation:\n  [0.23, -0.45, 0.78, ..., 0.12] (32 numbers)\n  (captures essence of the image)\n\nDecoder:\n  Layer 1: 32 → 64 units\n  Layer 2: 64 → 128 units\n  Output: 128 → 784 units (reconstructed)\n\nReconstructed Image:\n  28×28 pixels = 784 dimensions\n  (approximate copy of original)\n\nLoss: Compare original vs. reconstructed pixels"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefits of Encoder/Decoder in Autoencoders"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefit"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Explanation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Unsupervised learning"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Learns representations without labeled data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Efficient compression"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reduces data dimensionality while preserving essence"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Feature learning"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Automatically extracts important features"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Noise reduction"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Can reconstruct cleaner versions of noisy input"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Flexible architecture"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Adaptable to images, text, audio, financial data"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs & Limitations"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Limitation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Explanation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Lossy reconstruction"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Output is never perfect copy of input"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Quality depends on model"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Depends on model complexity and data quality"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Bottleneck size critical"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Too small = loses information; too large = doesn't compress"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Overfitting risk"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model might learn to copy input without learning features"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental Model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of encoder/decoder as a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "story summarization game"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Encoder"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = You read a 10-page story and write a 1-page summary"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Bottleneck"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = The 1-page summary (compressed representation)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Decoder"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Someone else reads your summary and tries to tell the story back to you"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Goal"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = The reconstructed story should closely match the original"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Or think of it as a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ZIP file"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Encoder"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Compressing a folder into a ZIP file (784 bytes → 32 bytes)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Bottleneck"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = The ZIP file (tiny but contains all essential info)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Decoder"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Extracting the ZIP file back to original folder (32 bytes → 784 bytes)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Loss"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Some files might be slightly corrupted during compression/decompression"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Encoder"}, {"type": "text", "text": " compresses input data into a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "lower-dimensional latent representation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (e.g., 784 → 32 units)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Decoder"}, {"type": "text", "text": " reconstructs original data from the compressed representation (e.g., 32 → 784 units)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Bottleneck"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (latent space) is the narrowest part holding the most compact, distilled version of data"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Decoder mirrors encoder"}, {"type": "text", "text": " but in reverse: if encoder reduces units, decoder increases them"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training goal"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Minimize difference between input "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "X"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " and reconstruction "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "X'"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " (e.g., MSE loss)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Unsupervised learning"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Learns efficient data representations without labels"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Applications"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Image compression, noise removal, feature extraction, anomaly detection, data generation"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Lossy reconstruction"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Output is an approximate copy, not perfect"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Encoder/Decoder in autoencoders enables learning compact data representations that can be used for compression, generation, and feature extraction—fundamental building blocks for many generative AI systems."}]}]}}